messages.original: Geran-2 drones are now entering Moldovan Airspace.   Additional Gerans are flying through Belarus towards Warsaw, Poland.
The numbers of Gerans flying through Belarusian airspace are unknown, but it could be anywhere from 5 to 13. Belarusian Su-30s are airborne in roughly the same area as the drones.
Polish fighter jets are heard over the city of Lublin, eastern Poland.
It seems 8 Tu-95s from Engels-2 Airbase are airborne. Those are all of the bombers at the airbase. Not all of them will launch missiles.
2 Tu-95MS strategic bombers landed at Engels-2 Airbase. No missile launches have been recorded.
No drone flights have been reported in Polish airspace for the past 10 minutes.
A U.S. Airforce F-35 was just refueled by an Airbus A330-243 near Mielec, southeastern Poland.

Reportedly photos from the scene of a downed Russian Geran-2 drone in the city of Zamo≈õƒá, eastern Poland. 
As of now, Polish airspace appears to be clear of aerial targets.

Polish airspace is now confirmed to be fully clear of drones. The remaining ones were shot down by aviation from several different countries. 
The remaining Geran-2 drones in western Ukraine are attacking the cities of Lviv and Rivne.

Warsaw International Airport has temporarily closed due to ‚Äúunplanned military activity related to ensuring state security‚Äù
2 of the Tu-95s that departed from Engels-2 Airbase earlier are carrying out a training mission in northern Saratov Oblast and are not expected to launch any missiles.
The remaining Tu-95s have landed at Diaghilev and Olenya Airbases. No missiles were launched.

In the Prosyana direction, Russian forces resumed their assault operations and improved their positions in the direction of Andriivka-Klevstove.
Russian forces advanced from in and around Tolstoi, west to the rest of the orchards and took up new positions in the treelines there. As a result, Ukrainian forces withdrew back into Andriivka-Klevstove, where a large grey zone has formed in front of it that neither side can hold a permanent presence in. 
+ ~9.75 km¬≤ in favour of Russia.

In the Novopavlivka direction, Russian forces resumed their assault operations and have recaptured previously lost positions in two areas.
In the north, around five days ago, Russian forces advanced from the area of Novomykolaivka, across the bridge over the tributary of the Solona River, and entered the eastern houses of Muravka. They were able to secure positions in at least a dozen buildings here. Meanwhile, other forces attacked from the treeline running to Muravka from the south and entered its southern street, linking up with formations in the eastern houses of the village. As a result, around 40% of Muravka is under Russian control, with the main Ukrainian presence confined to the northwestern part. 
In the south, Russian forces began pushing back towards the Donetsk-Dnipropetrovsk regional border. They recaptured trenches in the vicinity of the reservoir southwest of Kotlyrarivka, and advanced up the adjacent treeline to the north. 
+ ~3.09 km¬≤ in favour of Russia.
Warsaw International Airport has temporarily closed due to ‚Äúunplanned military activity related to ensuring state security‚Äù
Warsaw airport has been reopened.

In the Kostyantynivka direction, both Russian and Ukrainian forces have advanced, with Russian forces making important progress towards Nelipivka.
After consolidating in the area of the Terykon, Russian forces began attacking north towards Nelipivka, where they have approached the village. They were able to capture positions along the highway, as well as in the nearby forest plantations. 
Meanwhile, after nearly two weeks of positional battles, Ukrainian forces were able to advance past Zelena Street in the centre of Kleban-Byk and pushed Russian forces back to the southern edge of the village, where they recaptured the local school and hospital.
+ ~2.85 km¬≤ in favour of Russia.
+ ~0.20 km¬≤ in favour of Ukraine.
2 Tu-95MS strategic bombers departed from Engels-2 Airbase, Saratov Oblast.

In the Lyman direction, Russian forces continue to advance and have made new advances in three areas.
In the south, after securing most of the Serebryanksyi Forest, Russian forces advanced across the Zherebets River at a new point, and entered the forests south of Zarichne. They were able to advance west for approximately 2.3 km, capturing numerous new positions. Russian soldiers are now operating int he area of the Zarichne - Yampil Road, but no consolidation has occurred there yet. 
To the north, Russian forces continued to advance in Zarichne and have managed to break through to the western outskirts. They advanced west down Tsentralna Street and captured positions towards its western edge. Positions were also captured on the streets to the north and south, as well as at the local school and church in the village centre.
In the north, Russian forces continued to expand their bridgehead in northern Zarichne, and are approaching the Stavky - Zarichne Road. Here, they were able to deepen their zone of control along Poshtova and Chapayeva Streets, putting the remaining Ukrainian positions in the northern part of the village in a salient.
+ ~5.71 km¬≤ in favour of Russia.
2 Tu-95MS strategic bombers departed from Engels-2 Airbase, Saratov Oblast.
Currently 3 Tu-95s are circling in the area of Engels-2 Airbase.
